IsPartner.title: Partner Account
IsPartner.description: Indicates whether the account has at least one contact enabled to use the org's partner portal (true) or not (false). This field is available if partner relationship management (partner portal) is enabled OR digital experiences is enabled and you have partner portal licenses.If you change this field's value from true to false, you can disable up to 15 partner portal users associated with the account and permanently delete all of the account's partner portal roles and groups. You can't restore deleted partner portal roles and groups. Disabling a partner portal user in the Salesforce user interface or the API doesnâ€™t change this field's value from true to false. Even if this field's value is false, you can enable a contact on an account as a partner portal user via the API. Exclude this field when merging accounts. This field can be updated in API version 16.0 and later. Tip We recommend that you update up to 50 contacts simultaneously when changing the accounts on contacts enabled for an Experience Cloud site. We also recommend that you make this update after business hours.

IsCustomerPortal.title: Customer Portal Account
IsCustomerPortal.description: Indicates whether the account has at least one contact enabled to use the org's Experience Cloud site or Customer Portal (true) or not (false). This field is available if Customer Portal is enabled OR digital experiences is enabled.If your org is enabled to use Content Security Policy (CSP) features, then this field is visible on the Account object even if those features are later disabled. If you change this field's value from true to false, you can disable up to 100 Experience Cloud site or Customer Portal users associated with the account and permanently delete all of the account's site roles and groups. You can't restore deleted site roles and groups. Exclude this field when merging accounts. This field can be updated in API version 16.0 and later. Tip We recommend that you update up to 50 contacts simultaneously when changing the accounts on contacts enabled for an Experience Cloud site. We also recommend that you make this update after business hours.

schema.description: [Core] Represents a warehouse, service vehicle, work site, or other element of the region where your team performs field service work. In API version 49.0 and later, you can associate activities with specific locations. Activities, such as the tasks and events related to a location, appear in the activities timeline when you view the location detail page. Also in API version 49.0 and later, Work.com users can view Employees as a related list on Location records. In API version 51.0 and later, this object is available for Omnichannel Inventory and represents physical locations where inventory is available for fulfilling orders.

Id.title: Location ID
Id.description: Globally unique string that identifies a record.

Name.title: Location Name
Name.description: The name of the location. For example, Service Van #4.

LastModifiedDate.title: Last Modified Date
LastModifiedDate.description: Date and time when a user last modified this record.

LocationType.title: Location Type
LocationType.description: Picklist of location types. It has no default values, so you must populate it before creating any location records.

Description.title: Description
Description.description: A brief description of the location.

PossessionDate.title: Possession Date
PossessionDate.description: The date the location was purchased.

ConstructionStartDate.description: Date construction began at the location.

ConstructionEndDate.title: Construction End Date
ConstructionEndDate.description: Date construction ended at the location.

OpenDate.title: Open Date
OpenDate.description: Date the location opened or came into service.

CloseDate.title: Close Date
CloseDate.description: Date the location closed or went out of service.

RemodelStartDate.title: Remodel Start Date
RemodelStartDate.description: Date when remodel construction started at the location.

RemodelEndDate.title: Remodel End Date
RemodelEndDate.description: Date when remodel construction ended at the location.

IsMobile.title: Mobile Location
IsMobile.description: Indicates whether the location moves. For example, a truck or tool box.

IsInventoryLocation.title: Inventory Location
IsInventoryLocation.description: Indicates whether the location stores parts. Note This field must be selected if you want to associate the location with product items.

LocationLevel.title: Location Level
LocationLevel.description: The locationâ€™s position in a location hierarchy. If the location has no parent or child locations, its level is 1. Locations that belong to a hierarchy have a level of 1 for the root location, 2 for the child locations of the root location, 3 for their children, and so forth.

ShouldSyncWithOci.title: Sync with OCI
ShouldSyncWithOci.description: Indicates whether the location should sync its data with Omnichannel Inventory. The default value is false.

Priority.title: Priority
Priority.description: The priority of the location when routing orders. No default values are included. Add values to the picklist and reference them in your custom routing logic.

FoCapacity.title: Fulfillment Order Capacity

data.description: Represents a warehouse, service vehicle, work site, or other element of the region where your team performs field service work. In API version 49.0 and later, you can associate activities with specific locations. Activities, such as the tasks and events related to a location, appear in the activities timeline when you view the location detail page. Also in API version 49.0 and later, Work.com users can view Employees as a related list on Location records. In API version 51.0 and later, this object is available for Omnichannel Inventory and represents physical locations where inventory is available for fulfilling orders.
